Class SpeciesValidationFilter

java.lang.Object
  gnat.filter.nei.SpeciesValidationFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Filter
public class SpeciesValidationFilter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Filter

Checks if the given gene is indeed discussed together (same sentence, same clause, ...) with the given species.

Input: gene ID, taxon ID, sentence, previous sentence, sentence0=title, sentence1=first sentence, abstract
Output: true or false...

Removes wrongly assigned gene IDs the candidate IDs of a RecognizedGeneName.
Ideas:

  • if the gene occurs in a sentence where another species is mentioned but not the given one, invalidate the ID


Requirements:
Needs information on each gene (such as species), thus requires a loaded GeneRepository.

Author:
Joerg

The minimum filtering method that has to be implemented. A Run will call this method for each filter in sequence.
Each filter can read and potentially change context, textRepository, and geneRepository in this method.
